üßë‚Äçüíª Modular Machine Learning Pipeline
üìä Dataset Used
‚Ä¢	Dataset: Breast Cancer Wisconsin (Diagnostic) Dataset
‚Ä¢	Source: sklearn.datasets.load_breast_cancer()
‚Ä¢	Description: The dataset contains 569 samples with 30 features, representing tumor characteristics. Target variable indicates whether the tumor is malignant (1) or benign (0).
________________________________________
‚öôÔ∏è Steps Included in the Pipeline
1.	Data Loading Module
o	Loads dataset from sklearn.
o	Handles missing values (if any).
2.	Preprocessing Module
o	Encodes categorical features (if present).
o	Scales features using StandardScaler.
o	Splits dataset into training and testing sets.
3.	Model Training Module
o	Supports supervised ML models (Logistic Regression, Decision Tree, Random Forest).
o	Ensures reproducibility using random_state.
4.	Evaluation Module
o	Computes Accuracy, Precision, Recall, and F1-score.
o	Displays Confusion Matrix.
o	Prints full Classification Report.
________________________________________

‚ñ∂Ô∏è How to Run the Code
1.	Clone this repository:
2.	git clone https://github.com/your-username/ml-pipeline.git
3.	cd ml-pipeline
4.	Install dependencies:
5.	pip install -r requirements.txt
6.	Run the pipeline script:
7.	python ml_pipeline.py
8.	Results will include:
o	Evaluation metrics (Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-score).
o	Confusion Matrix plot.
o	Classification report.


